header.gameNote: BTI TIP-OFF TOURNAMENT AT CEDAR FALLS IA

article.headline: Cal Poly-SLO 88, N. Illinois 78
article.story: CEDAR FALLS, Iowa (AP) -- Trae Clark scored a game high 22 points to lead CalPoly to an 88-78 win over Northern Illinois on Sunday in the BTI Tipoff Tournament. CalPoly (1-2) took control of the game with a 13-4 run midway through the second half. Clark scored six straight points during that stretch at the free-throw line as the Mustangs built their largest lead of the game at 70-54. Northern Illinois (0-3) answered with a 20-8 run to cut the margin to 78-74. Ryan Paradise scored 21 points to lead four Northern Illinois players in double figures. Foul trouble plagued the Huskies, who had four players foul out.
